-- 
Swiss Stocks Gain as Citigroup Raises Bank Sector Recommendation

-- B y   P e t e r   L e v r i n g
-- 
2011-05-27T16:04:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/swiss-stocks-gain-as-citigroup-raises-bank-sector-recommendation.html
Swiss stocks gained for a fourth
straight day, led by banks after Citigroup Inc. recommended
European banking shares.  UBS AG (UBSN) ,  Switzerland ’s biggest bank, climbed 1.2 percent as
Citigroup raised European banks to “overweight.”  The  Swiss Market Index (SMI)  of the biggest and most actively
traded companies rose 0.3 percent to 6,489.32 at the 5:30 p.m.
close in Zurich. The measure lost 0.6 percent this week. The
broader Swiss Performance Index also gained 0.3 percent today.  In the U.S., a report today showed that consumer sentiment
increased in May. The Thomson Reuters/University of Michigan
final consumer confidence gauge increased to 74.3 in May from
69.8 in April, the group reported today. A separate release
today showed that  consumer spending  cooled in April as purchases
increased 0.4 percent, their smallest advance in three months.  UBS gained 1.2 percent to 16.28 Swiss francs after
Citigroup said the probability of a selloff in the industry from
current share prices was low.  Syngenta AG (SYNN)  gained 0.6 percent to 289.30 francs.  Holcim
Ltd. (HOLN)  climbed 0.6 percent to 67.40 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Levring in Copenhagen at 
